LAGOS – More often than not, distrust rages the air that surrounds many Nigerian businesses. In this part of the world, most ventures die, primarily not because of the harsh economic environment, but self-inflicted and eternal injuries too deep to heal. But the dynamics are changing. Revolutionary young entrepreneurs like Okeke Chibuikem Sinclair, CEO of Clairhub, Nigeria’s trusted digital cryptocurrency company, are earning the unshakable confidence of clients. “At Clairhub, we have established our name as a trusted and reliable crypto trader, that is why our customer base is growing by the day”, Okeke Sinclair stated. Speaking further, the founder ofClairhub said, “We don’t just buy or sell crypto for customers, Clairhub also help manage customers’ digital assets and we organise cryptocurrency trading training for them as well. “Clairhub is an enterprise aimed at bringing ease and transparency to people looking to exchange their crypto currency for cash as well as reliable social media services”, added the managing director of Clairhub. Continuing, the owner of Clairhub said, “however, an astute investor needs a trusted crypto trader to avoid being duped by internet fraudsters and crypto thieves who are out there in their numbers. “At Clairhub, we have established our name as a trusted and reliable crypto trader, that is why our customer base is growing by the day”. POLL For Clairhub, it begins with the vision behind the company. Hackers and online theft of digital currencies and assets have increased in the same proportion as technological innovations. Tech guru, Okeke Chibuikem Sinclair, was moved by passion to create sanity in the crypto space, by ensuring that clients no longer fall victims of online prying eyes. “I started this business because of the high rate scammers and business with an unfavourable rates and customer service. Risks might include new government rules, volatile rates, hacks etc,” declared the Clairhub CEO.